    "type": "markdown",
    "source": "#### HelpSteer Dataset Format\nThis format uses numeric preference scores to indicate which response is better. The context can be either a simple string or an array of message objects.\n\nRequired fields:\n- **`context`**: The input context (can be a string or array of message objects)\n- **`response1`**: First response option\n- **`response2`**: Second response option\n- **`overall_preference`**: Preference score where negative values mean response1 is preferred, positive values mean response2 is preferred, and 0 indicates a tie",
    "source_html": "<h4>HelpSteer Dataset Format</h4>\n<p>This format uses numeric preference scores to indicate which response is better. The context can be either a simple string or an array of message objects.</p>\n<p>Required fields:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><code>context</code></strong>: The input context (can be a string or array of message objects)</li>\n<li><strong><code>response1</code></strong>: First response option</li>\n<li><strong><code>response2</code></strong>: Second response option</li>\n<li><strong><code>overall_preference</code></strong>: Preference score where negative values mean response1 is preferred, positive values mean response2 is preferred, and 0 indicates a tie</li>\n</ul>\n"
